```java
public Class getGenericType(Field field) {        
    Type generic = field.getGenericType();
    if (generic != null && generic instanceof ParameterizedType) {
        Type actual = ((ParameterizedType) generic).getActualTypeArguments()[0];
        if (actual instanceof Class) {
            return (Class) actual;
        } else if (actual instanceof ParameterizedType) {
            return (Class) ((ParameterizedType) actual).getRawType();
        } else {
            return Object.class;
        }
    }
    
    return Object.class;
}
```

This preserves the original behavior for simple cases (e.g., `List<String>` where `actual` is `String.class`), and handles nested generics by returning the raw type (e.g., for `List<List<String>>`, returns `List.class`). Also handles other cases by returning `Object.class`.

